content: Love the random mute feature! Also really intuitive for using in compound time signatures with custom groupings.

I love the simplicity of this app and the fact that you can use multiple time signatures in a queue, but I wish you could change the click rate without changing the time signature. To elaborate, right now the click of the metronome follows the time signature (4/4 time signature = 1/4 note click). It would be nice to have an 1/8 or 1/16 note click with an accent on the 1 of the bar instead of being limited to a click rate which is tied to the time signature.

4.99 stars. The only small gripe is me wishing it would also display a little running timer for a quick easy reference. Other than that it's fantastic. Simple. Straight forward. Awesome and easy drop out feature that can be very helpful.

content: June 9th all presets gone again Remember, in Oreo going forward, any data stored internally created by an app will be deleted upon uninstall of that app AND if updates are not handled properly (such aa when having the packager uninstall, then reinstall the updates version, rather than the Google-required side loading method!) So u side load, u dont uninstall/install new update? Your Pixel is Oreo or Pie? You dont offer a choice where we save presets, can you?
replyContent: Dan, I'm glad that the crash issue was resolved with todays update, but I have no idea why you would have lost presets. This did not happen on my device (Pixel), nor any other device or simulator we tried the app on. Unfortunately, we can't fix what we can't recreate. I'm very sorry for the preset loss though.

content: the only improvements I would suggest is to enter the bpm value from a dial pad as well. it is only available from the slider and the arrows and it's quite inconvenient. also it would be great if there was an option for 32nds (because of the fact that there is the option for 16nths septuplets and they are so close each other)

The app is amazing but there's one very annoying flaw. When changing the tempo long pressing the left and right buttons, Unlike the ios version where it jumps to numbers ending in 5 or 0 (0,5,10,15..), on the Android version it jumps by 1 and then jumps by consecutive 5s. This jumping system makes no sense and makes it harder to reach the desired tempo. Please fix this ~~~. Other than that the app is fantastic. I'll 5☆ once this is fixed!

content: Won't give it 5 stars, because I only bought it for the ability to mute bars...which took a minute to figure out honestly, but only because of my ineptness. Also, while 16 measures seems generous I feel limited by it. Some ideas to consider: -"Clear" button -"Undo" button -Some way to re-order entered measures (tap, hold, & drag?) -Some way to change the number of beats in a measure without deleting (scrub left/right?)

Would be willing to pay more if I were able to make longer presets for beats - to use for the entirety of one excerpt where meters change often. I'd love to cue up Rite of Spring in this, but the presets are too short!!!
Whoops, my bad... I love this metronome!

content: The best app for building consistent time. I have been using Time Guru for years now and I constantly recommend it to students and peers alike.

I'm not surprised that this is an excellent app, because Avi is a phenomenal musician, not to mention being extremely funky! I was looking for something with the training element, and this does that beautifully. I'm also delighted that you can easily combine measures of different lengths. Tons of great sounds, even voices in different languages! Wow. The only thing it doesn't do that I like is picking several accents per measure for flamenco, but I have another metronome for that.   I was puzzled that people are griping about not being able to change the sound of that 1st beat in a measure. I wonder if they're just selecting "1" as the meter? Logically, that gives no accent. If you pick any number higher than "1", then the first beat is noticeably different. Admittedly some sounds may have a less obvious "one", but it's there. Maybe they meant actually putting a totally different sound on "one" to make it super obvious - it doesn't allow that.  Avi, fabulous job!!!!!!!
Very useful app, graduated muting for developing your internal clock. Agree with comment re needing different sound for first beat of bar
